title: Temu, fascinating array of products!
text:
I have purchased several dozen items, most that I never knew I needed. These simple novelty items came in  handy as I kept a few myself, mostly gave them away to friends as  “gifts”. The quality of some items I found to be extraordinary, and others just completely unacceptable, in which case I was able to either return, or get a credit for without any problems from Temu. 
My main gripe would be that the pictures always seem to show the item as larger and more complete than when you receive same, many disappointments on that level.
The best advice, be very careful, and read every description in detail, or you will be surprised at what you receive, disappointed would be a better description.

title: Loved this
text: 𝑨𝒑𝒑𝒍𝒚 𝑻𝒆𝒎𝒖 𝑪𝒐𝒖𝒑𝒐𝒏 𝑪𝒐𝒅𝒆 “𝑨𝑷𝑳𝟐𝟏𝟓𝟓𝟐” 𝒊𝒏 𝒑𝒓𝒐𝒇𝒊𝒍𝒆 𝒔𝒆𝒄𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏 𝒕𝒐 𝒈𝒆𝒕 $𝟏𝟎𝟎. It's great for the price tags but the user interface is poor, with random pop-ups that you can't skip over. The instructions for deleting an account were inaccurate and it took forever to even find the button to do so. Customer service was hard to communicate with and I'm fairly certain the "person" I chatted with was Al; I was met with repeated questions and statements in the exact same manner and it was a long and difficult process to get a refund on an item that I never received. The big sales like Black Friday are more often than not scams; they entice you by claiming to offer free gifts of your choosing but afterward make you invite new users to the app or perform other tasks to get the rewards. Even after inviting new users, the "points" per person dwindles with each accepted invitation to the point where no matter how many people accept your link, you still can't claim the gifts you chose; they use you to get new customers and more traffic while giving you nothing in return. Plus, the obscured data collection and hidden features that you often unknowingly "consent" to by simply pressing a seemingly harmless button makes for a very sketchy platform. That's not even to mention the poor packaging and shipment; everything gets thrown into a bag that is haphazardly taped up. My advice is use at your own risk and don't partake in deals that seem too good to be true- most often, they are.

title: Best shopping app
text: With our current economy Temu is the only way I have been able to start replacing our decade old wardrobe. I’ve also found some nice sensory items for a couple of my kids. I’ve only received a small handful of items that weren’t what they appeared to be or the sizing was wrong. Customer support is better than anywhere else too! The money for those items was quickly returned and I was able to donate them to the homeless community. That’s an AMAZING thing! I have two suggestions though. I wear an extra small in tops and the selection in that size is VERY limited. I would like more of the women’s clothing to be available in an extra small. Also, I think we would all benefit from some type of organization in our carts. Maybe categories like ‘for me’ ‘for Hollidays’ ‘for house’ or even something as simple as being able to rearrange the items in the cart. I’ve had over $700 of stuff in my cart that I would slowly buy as I could afford it. I would have to scroll through the ENTIRE cart to select the items I needed to buy first. If we could simply hold and drag items in the cart to reorganize them it would be HUGELY beneficial to MOST of the people who use this app. I literally bought our entire Christmas from temu this past year and it was difficult to order each payday because I would have to look through the cart to find the items I could afford or were most important. It’s pretty time consuming. ALOT of people see something they like or want and hit ‘add to cart’ so they can save it for later. When it’s time to actually buy those things it’s a bit frustrating that we can’t even organize those ‘to buy’ items. Please add some type of organizing feature. Thank you so much for making it possible to afford gifts for friends and family as well as clothing for my entire household.
